{"title_page": "Peter Lundgren (politician)", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name      = Peter Lundgren\n|honorific-suffix = [[Member of the European Parliament|MEP]]\n|image     = Peter Lundgren (politiker).jpg\n|office     = Vice-Chair of the [[European Conservatives and Reformists|European<br />Conservatives and Reformists Group]]\n|term_start      = 2 July 2019\n| 1blankname       =  Co-chairs\n| 1namedata        = [[Raffaele Fitto]]<br>[[Ryszard Legutko]]\n| 1blankname1       = Serving alongside\n| 1namedata1        = [[Roberts Z\u012ble]]<br/>[[Assita Kanko]]<br/>[[Daniel Hannan]]<br/>[[Derk Jan Eppink]]<br>[[Hermann Tertsch]]\n|term_end      =  \n|constituency       = \n|office2     = [[Member of the European Parliament]]\n|term_start2      = 1 July 2014\n|term_end2      =  \n|constituency2       = [[Sweden (European Parliament constituency)|Sweden]]\n|birth_name      = Kent Peter Lundgren\n|birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1963|2|2|df=yes}}\n|birth_place     = [[Ekeby, Bjuv]], [[Sk\u00e5ne County]], [[Sweden]]\n|death_date     = \n|death_place      = \n|party      = '''''{{flag|Sweden|name=Swedish}}'''''<br />[[Sweden Democrats]]<br />'''''{{flag|EU}}'''''<br />[[European Conservatives and Reformists]]\n|spouse       =\n|children       =\n|alma_mater     = \n|website     = \n}}\n\n'''Kent Peter Lundgren''' (born 2 February 1963) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[politician]] and [[Member of the European Parliament]] (MEP) from [[Sweden]]. He is a member of the [[Sweden Democrats]], part of [[European Conservatives and Reformists]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europaportalen.se/2014/03/ser-sig-inte-som-europe |title=SD-kandidat: Jag vill avveckla EU |language=Swedish |publisher=europaportalen.se |accessdate=2014-05-26}}</ref>\n\nLundgren was elected as [[Member of the European Parliament]] (MEP) in the [[2014 European Parliament election in Sweden|May 2014 European Parliament election in Sweden]]. He was re-elected [[Member of the European Parliament]] in the [[2019 European Parliament election in Sweden]].<ref>[https://data.val.se/val/ep2019/slutresultat/E/rike/personroster.html Final results from European Parliament elections in Sweden] Read 2019-05-31 (in Swedish)</ref>\n\n==Career==\nLundgren is a former [[truck driver]]. He has been a member of the [[executive board]] of the [[Sweden Democrats]] since November 2013.  Lundgren was launched as one of his party's top candidates to the [[European Parliament]] on 27 January 2014. On 25 May 2014, Lundgren and [[Kristina Winberg]] became the first representatives of the Sweden Democrats to be elected [[Member of the European Parliament|Members of the European Parliament]].<ref>{{cite news |last=H\u00f6gstr\u00f6m |first=Erik |last2=Baas |first2=David |last3=Julander |first3=Oscar |url=http://www.expressen.se/nyheter/val2014/succe-for-sd--tar-plats-i-parlamentet/ |title=Succ\u00e9 f\u00f6r SD \u2013 tar plats i parlamentet &#124; Val 2014 |newspaper=[[Expressen]] |date=2014-05-25 |accessdate=2014-05-26 |language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=91&artikel=5872166 |title=B\u00e5de Lundgren och Winberg till Bryssel |publisher=[[Sveriges Radio]] |date=2014-04-25 |language=Swedish }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Duxbury |first=Charles |url=https://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304811904579584420694958010 |title=Top Two Swedish Parties Lose Ground in European Vote |work=The Wall Street Journal |accessdate=2014-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.europeonline-magazine.eu/extrasweden-democrats-win-two-of-swedens-20-seats_337773.html |title=EXTRA Sweden Democrats win two of Sweden's 20 seats |publisher=europeonline-magazine.eu |accessdate=2014-05-26}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Lundgren was one of the nominees for the [[Parliament Magazine]] award as the best EU parliamentarian in the [[transport]] section.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europaportalen.se/2015/02/tva-svenskar-nominerade-som-basta-eu-parlamentariker|title=Tv\u00e5 svenskar nominerade som b\u00e4sta EU-parlamentariker|date=2 February 2015|publisher=|accessdate=4 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mepawards.eu/shortlist|title=Shortlist - MEP Awards|date=13 April 2015|accessdate=4 July 2017|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413122046/http://www.mepawards.eu/shortlist|archivedate=13 April 2015}}</ref> This was the very first nominee from the [[EFDD]] group. Lundgren did not win the award but said he was happy to be nominated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vn.se/article/ingen-vinst-for-lundgren-sd/|title=Ingen vinst f\u00f6r Lundgren (SD)|first=Emilia|last=Lindholm|date=19 March 2015|publisher=vn.se|accessdate=4 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his re-election to the [[European Parliament]] in 2019, Lundgren was elected one of six Vice-Chairs of the [[European Conservatives and Reformists|European Conservatives and Reformists Group]].<ref>[http://www.europarl.europa.eu/meps/en/124996/PETER_LUNDGREN/history/9 Peter Lundgren at European Parliament webside] 2019-07-06</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe lives in [[Kulltorp]] and was member of the [[city council]] in [[Gnosj\u00f6 Municipality]] until his election to the [[European Parliament]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lindholm |first=Emilia |url=http://www.varnamonyheter.se/artikel/21036/peter-lundgren-kandiderar-till-europaparlamentet |title=Peter Lundgren kandiderar till Europaparlamentet |newspaper=V\u00e4rnamo Nyheter |language=Swedish  |date=2014-01-27 |accessdate=2014-05-26}}</ref> Peter Lundgren allegedly sexually assaulted a female colleague at a party event, this led to a larger scandal during the 2019 European election. <ref>{{cite news|last=Amorelli |first=Elisa |url=https://www.svd.se/peter-lundgren-tafsade--far-sitta-kvar |title=Peter Lundgren sexually assaulted \u2013 allowed to remain a candidate |newspaper=Svenska Dagbladet |language=Swedish  |date=2019-05-20 |accessdate=2019-07-10}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lundgren, Peter}}\n\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Bjuv Municipality]]\n[[Category:Sweden Democrats MEPs]]\n[[Category:MEPs for Sweden 2014\u20132019]]\n[[Category:MEPs for Sweden 2019\u20132024]]\n\n{{Sweden-MEP-stub}}{{Current EP Sweden}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name      = Peter Lundgren\n|honorific-suffix = [[Member of the European Parliament|MEP]]\n|image     = Peter Lundgren (politiker).jpg\n|office     = Vice-Chair of the [[European Conservatives and Reformists|European<br />Conservatives and Reformists Group]]\n|term_start      = 2 July 2019\n| 1blankname       =  Co-chairs\n| 1namedata        = [[Raffaele Fitto]]<br>[[Ryszard Legutko]]\n| 1blankname1       = Serving alongside\n| 1namedata1        = [[Roberts Z\u012ble]]<br/>[[Assita Kanko]]<br/>[[Daniel Hannan]]<br/>[[Derk Jan Eppink]]<br>[[Hermann Tertsch]]\n|term_end      =  \n|constituency       = \n|office2     = [[Member of the European Parliament]]\n|term_start2      = 1 July 2014\n|term_end2      =  \n|constituency2       = [[Sweden (European Parliament constituency)|Sweden]]\n|birth_name      = Kent Peter Lundgren\n|birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1963|2|2|df=yes}}\n|birth_place     = [[Ekeby, Bjuv]], [[Sk\u00e5ne County]], [[Sweden]]\n|death_date     = \n|death_place      = \n|party      = '''''{{flag|Sweden|name=Swedish}}'''''<br />[[Sweden Democrats]]<br />'''''{{flag|EU}}'''''<br />[[European Conservatives and Reformists]]\n|spouse       =\n|children       =\n|alma_mater     = \n|website     = \n}}\n\n'''Kent Peter Lundgren''' (born 2 February 1963) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[politician]] and [[Member of the European Parliament]] (MEP) from [[Sweden]]. He is a member of the [[Sweden Democrats]], part of [[European Conservatives and Reformists]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europaportalen.se/2014/03/ser-sig-inte-som-europe |title=SD-kandidat: Jag vill